cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of voting systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an approach based on Risk-Limiting Audits, which involves statistical analysis and probability theory, making it relevant to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CY), and information theory (cs.IT).
